Adjacency Matrix</a></li><li><a href=3D"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/dsa/a=
djacency-matrix/#applications-of-adjacency-matrix">Applications of Adjacenc=
y Matrix:</a></li><li><a href=3D"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/dsa/adjacenc=
y-matrix/#advantages-of-adjacency-matrix">Advantages of Adjacency Matrix:</=
a></li><li><a href=3D"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/dsa/adjacency-matrix/#d=
isadvantages-of-adjacency-matrix">Disadvantages of Adjacency Matrix:</a></l=
i></ul></div><h2 id=3D"what-is-adjacency-matrix" style=3D"text-align:left">=
<span>What is Adjacency Matrix?</span></h2><p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"text-ali=
gn: start;"><span>Adjacency Matrix is a square matrix used to represent a f=
inite graph by storing the relationships between the nodes in their respect=
ive cells. For a graph with </span><b><strong>V</strong></b><span> vertices=
, the adjacency matrix A is an V</span><b><strong> X V </strong></b><span>m=
atrix or 2D array.</span></p><h2 id=3D"1-adjacency-matrix-for-undirected-an=
d-unweighted-graph" style=3D"text-align:left"><span>1. Adjacency Matrix for=
 Undirected and Unweighted graph:</span></h2><p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"text-a=
lign: start;"><span>Consider an Undirected and Unweighted graph </span><b><=
strong>G </strong></b><span>with </span><b><strong>4 vertices</strong></b><=
span> and </span><b><strong>3 edges</strong></b><span>. For the graph G, th=
e adjacency matrix would look like:</span></p><p dir=3D"ltr"><img src=3D"ht=
tps://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20240424142649/Adjacency-M=
atrix-for-Undirected-and-Unweighted-graph.webp" alt=3D"Adjacency-Matrix-for=
-Undirected-and-Unweighted-graph" width=3D"1043" height=3D"746"></p><p dir=
=3D"ltr" style=3D"text-align: start;"><span>Here's how to interpret the mat=
rix:</span></p><div id=3D"GFG_AD_Desktop_InContent_ATF_728x280" style=3D"te=
xt-align: center; margin: 10px 0px;"></div><ul><li value=3D"1"><b><strong>A=
[i][j] =E2=80=8B=3D 1,</strong></b><span> there is an edge between vertex i=
 and vertex j.</span></li><li value=3D"2"><b><strong>A[i][j] =E2=80=8B=3D 0=
,</strong></b><span> there is NO edge between vertex i and vertex j.</span>=
</li></ul><p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"text-align: start;"><span>Below is a prog=
ram to create an adjacency matrix for an unweighted and undirected graph:</=
span></p><gfg-tabs data-run-ide=3D"true" data-mode=3D"light" role=3D"tablis=
